replies.body:
As someone who started the game on Sejuani way back when I had no idea what I was doing and still play her to this day I agree with you.

IMO the easiest thing to do would be change the E to not be able to stack by allies.  Make it take 1 less hit, and only able to stack if Sejuani hits something or uses the W.  Then take the power that was smashed into the E and make it so the ultimate can freeze multiple targets again instead of just one.

Originally they said they wanted to give her more skill expression than being an ult bot, but the current version just turns her into an E bot instead where you mash the key through every team fight.  It's too powerful for a CC she can activate any time she wants just by being nearby, so they have to keep watering down her abilities to keep her on the edge of being mildly relevant yet not very good to actually play.  By that standard I would rather have the Sejuani that is actually fun to play back. {{champion:113}}
